what you learned.

17:03.524 --> 17:06.944
I think I learned that I wanna be
in a real relationship, Paige.

17:06.944 --> 17:07.778
With you.

17:07.778 --> 17:10.030
Yeah, I know, I know,
but you actually don't.

17:10.614 --> 17:12.658
Oh, really? How do you know that?

17:12.658 --> 17:14.451
Well, because
now I don't really want to be

17:14.451 --> 17:15.744
in a relationship with you,

17:15.744 --> 17:17.746
which makes me unavailably available.

17:17.746 --> 17:20.958
And so now you want
to be in a relationship with me?

17:22.709 --> 17:24.169
Okay, one of the sneakiest ways

17:24.169 --> 17:26.296
that unavailable people
keep themselves unavailable

17:26.296 --> 17:28.841
is by only being available to other people
who are unavailable.

17:28.841 --> 17:29.758
Does that make sense?

17:30.592 --> 17:31.927
Should I lie down?

17:31.927 --> 17:34.638
Oh, no, I-I have to go.

17:34.638 --> 17:36.431
I'm-I'm sorry. I just--

17:36.431 --> 17:39.351
I have this whole work thing,
and I have to get ready and--

17:39.351 --> 17:42.062
So, if you don't mind,
I think it would be good if you leave

17:42.062 --> 17:43.897
only because it's 5:30
and I have to be ready at 7:00.

17:43.897 --> 17:45.399
So, um,

17:46.900 --> 17:48.068
we're out of time.

17:49.278 --> 17:50.362
[sighs deeply]

17:52.281 --> 17:55.826
♪

18:11.758 --> 18:13.385
